One thing you'll notice in conversations about trans women specifically is the mysterious appearance of "several real women."

They're everywhere.

"Several real women told me..."

"Every woman I know thinks..."

"All the women I've spoken to agree..."

Somehow these women are never actually here. They never show up in the comments. They never speak for themselves. They exist exclusively as a ventriloquist dummy for whatever opinion the person already had...

The funny thing is that actual women are not a hive mind.

Some women support trans women.

Some women don't.

Most women are busy trying to survive late-stage capitalism and aren't spending their afternoons conducting focus groups about my existence...

And that's part of why I do what I do.

When I started talking publicly about being trans, I quickly realized that a lot of conversations about us happen without us. People debate what we think, what we feel, what we believe, and what our lives are supposedly like...

So I figured I'd just show up and speak for myself.

You don't have to agree with me.

You don't have to find me convincing.

But I think conversations get a lot healthier when we're talking to actual trans people instead of imaginary groups of "real women," "normal people," or whatever other crowd gets summoned to support an argument...

If someone has a criticism of me, they can make it themselves.

Dave doesn't need to bring twelve invisible women to court as character witnesses.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RHyWkUy.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Anyway, here is the video that scared Dave and those "women" so much...</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/dNhUvPP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Alsoashley]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The first time thoughts and prayers did anything! (D&amp;D)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/jH9x8AW</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/YWTJ4gV.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Animation: https://www.youtube.com/@PunkeyDoodles8
